article.headline: Tennessee St. 61, E. Illinois 58
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. (AP) -- Reiley Ervin scored 19 points to lead Tennessee State to a 61-58 win over Eastern Illinois on Saturday. The game featured five ties and 11 lead changes, and neither team led by more than six. Two free throws by Bobby Catchings cut the Tigers lead to 60-58 with 3:10 remaining. Both teams had several possessions the closing minutes, but weren't able to score. Ervin's free throw with 8 seconds left was the game's final point. Mike Robinson missed a 3-pointer at the buzzer that would have sent the game into overtime. Clarence Matthews scored 12 points and grabbed seven rebounds for Tennessee State (9-10, 5-4 Ohio Valley). Tennessee State shot 39.2 percent from the field, but converted 11-of-20 3-pointers. Eastern Illinois shot 40.4 percent, and went 6-for-16 from beyond the arc. Romain Martin scored 17 points to lead Eastern Illinois (5-16, 1-11).
